    <body>
      <group id="content" extype="content">
        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>Electronic payment management for vendor payments (Brazil)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve" extradata="MT" restype="x-metadata">
          <source>You can make electronic payments by transferring files between a legal entity and a bank.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Electronic payment management for vendor payments (Brazil)</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can make electronic payments by transferring files between a legal entity and a bank.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can generate and send an electronic remittance file to a bank.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this case, the export file contains information about invoices that must be received or paid, requests for return invoices, or changes to customer or vendor addresses.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Alternatively, you can import a return file from a bank.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In this case, the return file contains either information about the acceptance of an invoice together with the payment number that is provided by the bank, or information about the payments that are received from a customer or paid to a vendor.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This task uses the BRMF demo company.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="110" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Go to Purchase ledger &gt; Payments &gt; Payment transfers.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="111" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the list, mark the selected row.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="112" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Return file - vendor.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="113" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the Method of payment field, enter or select a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="114" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="115" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="116" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The status of the payments is updated in the Payments status field on the Payment transfers page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="117" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The new status is based on the status of the payment in the return file.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="118" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click Post.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="119" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>In the New journal name field, type a value.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="120" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Click OK.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="121" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Close the page.</source>
        </trans-unit>
